                <p>Here are some common commands you'll use while working with Django. If you can think of anything I should add, <a href="mailto:nick@zappycode.com">let me know!</a></p>
<h2>Creating a New Project</h2>
<pre class="rounded hljs"><code>
django-admin startproject projectname
    </code></pre>
<h2>Add an App to a Project</h2>
<pre class="rounded hljs properties"><code>
<span class="hljs-attr">python3</span> <span class="hljs-string">manage.py startapp appname</span>
    </code></pre>
<h2>Starting the server</h2>
<pre class="rounded hljs properties"><code>
<span class="hljs-attr">python3</span> <span class="hljs-string">manage.py runserver</span>
    </code></pre>
<h2>Creating Migrations</h2>
<pre class="rounded hljs properties"><code>
<span class="hljs-attr">python3</span> <span class="hljs-string">manage.py makemigrations</span>
    </code></pre>
<h2>Migrate the Database</h2>
<pre class="rounded hljs properties"><code>
<span class="hljs-attr">python3</span> <span class="hljs-string">manage.py migrate</span>
    </code></pre>
<h2>Creating a Super User for the Admin Panel</h2>
<pre class="rounded hljs properties"><code>
<span class="hljs-attr">python3</span> <span class="hljs-string">manage.py createsuperuser</span>
    </code></pre>
<h2>Change Any User's Password</h2>
<pre class="rounded hljs properties"><code>
<span class="hljs-attr">python3</span> <span class="hljs-string">manage.py changepassword</span>
    </code></pre>
<h2>Collecting Static Files Into One Folder</h2>
<pre class="rounded hljs properties"><code>
<span class="hljs-attr">python3</span> <span class="hljs-string">manage.py collectstatic</span>
    </code></pre>